msgstr ""

#: src/Form/ConfigForm.php:358
msgid "List of ips with open access, eventually limited to selected item sets"
msgstr ""

#: src/Form/ConfigForm.php:359
msgid ""
"List the ips separated by a \"=\", one by line. Range ip are allowed "
"(formatted as cidr). The value after \"=\" controls which item sets are "
"reachable:\n"
"- empty (no item set after \"=\"): the ip has unrestricted access to every "
"reserved resource, including resources that are not attached to any item "
"set;\n"
"- one or more item set ids: the ip has access only to resources attached to "
"at least one of these item sets; resources not in any item set are denied;\n"
"- an item set id prepended with \"-\" is an excluded item set, useful when a "
"global item set is defined to identify all reserved resources."
msgstr ""

#: src/Form/ConfigForm.php:383
msgid ""
"List of sso idp with open access, eventually limited to selected item sets"
msgstr ""

#: src/Form/ConfigForm.php:384
msgid ""
"List the identity providers separated by a \"=\", one by line. The idp name "
"is the entity id (or the value used in the login form). \"federation\" can "
"be used as fallback for all users authenticated via a federated idp not "
"listed above. The value after \"=\" controls which item sets are reachable:\n"
"- empty (no item set after \"=\"): the idp has unrestricted access to every "
"reserved resource, including resources that are not attached to any item "
"set;\n"
"- one or more item set ids: the idp has access only to resources attached to "
"at least one of these item sets; resources not in any item set are denied;\n"
"- an item set id prepended with \"-\" is an excluded item set, useful when a "
"global item set is defined to identify all reserved resources.\n"
"Without any matching entry (and no \"federation\" fallback), the user is "
"denied."
